 "role_id": 941, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "", "date_of_death": "", "genders": [], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2023-05-09T15:16:36.289730+10:00", "external_links": [], "uuid": "8389ac16-d751-4bdb-81a1-297a54791173", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "8733", "external_references": [{"id": 35831, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q121298852"}], "date_modified": "2023-09-05T20:13:33.338518+10:00"}, {"id": 36330, "name": "Jacques Doillon", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 3105063, "title": "La Drolesse = the Hussy", "work_id": 116226, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 1999265, "title": "Ponette", "work_id": 94362, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 3104722, "title": "Un Sac de Billes = a Bag of Marbles", "work_id": 116054, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 3104598, "title": "La Vie de Famille", "work_id": 115992, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 3104658, "title": "L'amoureuse = Women in Love", "work_id": 116020, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 3104725, "title": "Les Doigts Dans la Tete = Fingers in the Head", "work_id": 116056, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "1944-03-15", "date_of_death": null, "genders": [{"id": 9, "name": "Male", "slug": "male"}], "languages": [{"id": 4, "name": "French", "slug": "french"}], "places_of_operation": [{"id": 17, "name": "France", "slug": "france"}], "biography": "Jacques Doillon (French: [dwajɔ̃]; born 15 March 1944) is a French film director. He has a habit of giving lead roles to inexperienced young actresses in his films on family life and women. Some actresses to break through are Fanny Bastien, Sandrine Bonnaire, Judith Godrèche, Marianne Denicourt, Charlotte Gainsbourg and Juliette Binoche.\nDoillon was born in Paris. He has two daughters: Lola Doillon (born 1975), whose mother is film editor Noëlle Boisson, and Lou Doillon (born 1982), from his relationship with English actress Jane Birkin in the 1980s. He has three other children named Lili, Lina, and Lazare.\nHis 1989 film The 15 Year Old Girl was entered into the 16th Moscow International Film Festival.His 1990 film La vengeance d'une femme was entered into the 40th Berlin International Film Festival. The following year, his film Le Petit Criminel won an Honourable Mention at the 41st Berlin International Film Festival. In 1993, his film Le Jeune Werther won the Blue Angel Award at the 43rd Berlin International Film Festival. In 1998, his film Trop (peu) d'amour was entered into the 48th Berlin International Film Festival.", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2022-05-19T11:50:35.452367+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 2292, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jacques_Doillon"}], "uuid": "45d63d5f-4196-44fb-af7b-97debec1f8eb", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "21145", "external_references": [{"id": 9841, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q710650"}, {"id": 9842, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "117389627"}, {"id": 9843, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "n91076676"}, {"id": 9844, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-n91076676"}], "date_modified": "2025-05-22T22:56:03.593780+10:00"}]}